column2: Thank you very much for your cooperation! Please, kindly be informed that this survey is only for Malaysian participants. This is an anonymous survey that would take no more than 10 minutes to complete. We are a team of multinational researchers studying the effects of TRUST during a brief intervention at zero acquaintance. It is important that you rate each person in the videos objectively - specifically, how the information is expressed (the behaviour/action), and not what is said (the content of the message). Let's start!

column2: Introduzca sus preguntas por vídeo aquí
1. Indicate if you know/are familiar with the person in the video.
2. Assess the physical attractiveness of the person in the video.
3. Assess the person's voice attractiveness of the person in the video.
4. Assess the expressiveness of the person, whether he or she is energetic, intense, has an active body gesture.
5. Assess if you think that the person is comfortable in front of the camera.
6. Assess the kindness of the person, understanding kindness as a person that care about others, gentle, friendly and generous.
7. Assess whether the person is eloquent and articulate -- whether he or she expresses her/his opinion or feelings well.
8. What emotion do you think he/she is expressing?
9. Do you trust in the transmitted emotion? Does it seems credible, authentic?
10. Would you trust this person after seeing this video?
11. What would make you trust or distrust this person?
